      <h3>About BugLite</h3><br />
      <b>BugLite is the Engineering/CADD System's Office's (ECSO) latest Software Issue Tracking System</b>.
      The purpose for this application is to serve as a viable repository for creating, assigning, tracking, fixing, 
      and releasing development software specific issues or bugs.
      <br />
      <h3>Terms and Definitions</h3><br />
         1. Issue Statuses
         <br /><br />
         The following are the explanation for each of the standard statuses that are used with BugLite:
         <ul>
           <li><b class="open">Open</b> - indicates a new issue has been created and assigned to a team member.</li>
           <li><b class="inProgress">In Progress</b> - indicates that the issue is currently been worked on or assessed.</li>
           <li><b class="closed">Closed</b> - indicates that the issue has been completely fixed and no further actions are required on it.</li>
           <!--<li><b class="resolved">Resolved</b> - indicates that the issue has been fixed.</li>-->
         </ul>
         2. Priorities
         <br /><br />
         The following are the explanation for each of the standard priorities that are used with BugLite:
         <ul>
           <li><b class="critical">Critical</b> - indicates that the issue should be resolved immediately.</li>
           <li><b class="medium">High</b> - indicates that the issue should be resolved as soon as possible before the software is released.</li>
           <li><b class="high">Medium</b> - indicates that the issue should be resolved at a reasonable timeframe before the softare is released.</li>
           <li><b class="low">Low</b> - indicates that the issue can be resolved at a later date.</li>
         </ul>
